projects.name: Drug Traceability in Healthcare Supply Chain Using Blockchain
projects.description: The objective is to improve transparency, security, and efficiency in monitoring pharmaceutical products within the healthcare supply chain. The plan involves developing a Java-based blockchain framework, integrating it with existing systems, and evaluating its performance, security, and scalability. Case studies and comparisons with conventional methods will be conducted to confirm the solution's efficacy. The healthcare supply chain, with its complex network of entities, faces challenges such as a lack of information and centralized control, leading to inefficiencies and the entry of counterfeit drugs. The proposed blockchain solution aims to address these issues and enhance the overall effectiveness of the supply chain.

projects.name: Online Assignment Submission
projects.description: Online Assignment Submission System is a system that permits students to upload their assignments or projects online rather than sending a physical file. The proposed method aids teachers with the process of monitoring and handling students by eliminating and mitigating human error. Moreover, the proposed system allows supervisors to share documents and files with their students. Technologies: HTML, CSS, PHP, XAMPP, MYSQL, JS.
